17 analysis and other administrative tasks related to applying for and implementing the
18 waiver.
19 Existing law creates the Board of Directors of the Exchange which consists of:
20 (1) five voting members appointed by the Governor; (2) one voting member
21 appointed by the Majority Leader of the Senate; (3) one voting member appointed
22 by the Speaker of the Assembly; and (4) three ex officio, nonvoting members.
23 (NRS 695I.300) Section 3 of this bill: (1) requires the Majority Leader of the
24 Senate and the Speaker of the Assembly to each appoint one additional voting
25 member to the Board; and (2) makes a conforming change to the number of
26 members of the Board who must have certain expertise or experience to reflect the
27 increased number of members of the Board. Section 5 of this bill prescribes the
28 length of the initial terms of the new members added to the Board by section 3 to
29 ensure that the terms of the voting members of the Board are staggered.
