1 Section 1. Chapter 695I of NRS is hereby amended by adding
2 thereto a new section to read as follows:
3 1. The Legislature hereby finds and declares that it is the
4 public policy of this State that each natural person who otherwise
5 qualifies to purchase a qualified health plan on the Exchange,
6 regardless of his or her immigration or citizenship status, is
7 eligible to receive the benefits of purchasing a qualified health
8 plan on the Exchange.
9 2. The Executive Director, in collaboration with the Director
10 of the Department of Health and Human Services, the Director of
11 the Department of Business and Industry and the Commissioner,
12 shall:
13 (a) Conduct, or enter into a contract with an independent
14 actuary to conduct, an actuarial analysis to determine whether a
15 waiver described in paragraph (b) will meet the requirements of 42
16 U.S.C. § 18052(b); and
17 (b) If the actuarial analysis conducted pursuant to paragraph
18 (a) determines that the waiver will meet the requirements of 42
19 U.S.C. § 18052(b), apply to the Secretary of Health and Human
20 Services for a waiver pursuant to 42 U.S.C. § 18052 to authorize
21 any natural person to purchase a qualified health plan on the
22 Exchange, regardless of his or her immigration status, if the
23 natural person would otherwise be a qualified individual.
